== Roasted Veggies ==

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @bell pepper{1} lengthwise; remove stems and seeds. Halve @tomato{1} lengthwise. Peel @garlic{2%cloves}.

Toss bell pepper and tomato on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Push veggies to one side of sheet.

Place garlic cloves in the center of a small piece of #foil{}; drizzle with olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Cinch into a packet; place garlic foil packet on empty side of sheet.

Roast on top rack for ~{20%minutes} (you'll add more to the sheet in Step 5).

Meanwhile, trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise into ½-inch-thick rounds.

Toss zucchini on one side of a second baking sheet with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and place on empty side of sheet. Drizzle with @cooking oil{1%tsp} and season all over with salt and pepper.

Roast chicken and zucchini on middle rack until zucchini is tender and lightly browned and chicken is cooked through, ~{18-20%minutes}. Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}.

== Couscous ==

While chicken and zucchini roast, melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat.

Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%oz}; cook, stirring, until couscous is lightly toasted, ~{1-2%minutes}. Stir in ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4) and @chicken stock concentrate{1}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}; season with salt and pepper to taste.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Romesco Sauce ==

Once romesco veggies have roasted 20 minutes, remove sheet from oven. Transfer garlic foil packet to a #plate{} to cool.

Top romesco veggies on sheet with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}, @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @pepitas{1/2%oz}, and @smoked paprika{1%tsp}; season with salt and pepper. Carefully toss to combine.

Return to top rack and roast until panko and pepitas are lightly toasted, ~{8-10%minutes} more. Let cool for at least ~{5%minutes}.

Carefully transfer romesco mixture from sheet to a #blender{} or #food processor{} (be sure to scrape in any browned bits and liquid too!).

Remove roasted garlic from foil packet; add to blender.

Add half the @red wine vinegar{2.5%tsp}, 3 TBSP water, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, and @salt{1%tsp} to blender (use all the vinegar, 6 TBSP water, 4 TBSP olive oil, and 1 1/2 tsp salt for 4 servings).

Blend, scraping down the sides as needed, until mostly smooth, ~{1-2%minutes}. (If sauce seems too thick, blend in another 1-2 TBSP water.) Season romesco sauce generously with salt and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Spread as much romesco sauce as you like on one side of each #plate{}; fan chicken over top.

Divide couscous and roasted zucchini between plates in separate sections. Serve.

> TIP: Refrigerate any remaining romesco sauce in an airtight container for up to 5 days.

> Pro tip: Swipe leftover romesco sauce on your sandwich for a next-level flavor boost that can't be beat!

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.